<TITLE> Babar remand hearing set for Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka magistrate will hear on Wednesday the police appeal to remand BNP's former state minister for home Lutfozzaman Babar in custody for questioning The first additional chief metropolitan magistrate for Dhaka, Ehsanul Haque, will hear the appeal in presence of Babar. Babar, already behind bars, was shown arrested on Monday for the Aug 21 2004 grenade attack on an Awami league rally. Investigation officer, CID's Abdul Kahhar Akand, told bdnews24.com they had sought 10 days remand for the former state minister from the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court. Babar began serving 17 years on March 5 this year having been convicted in an arms case. The 2004 grenade attack on an Awami League rally at Bangabandhu Avenue killed at least 23 people and left scores injured, including then opposition leader Sheikh Hasina, now prime minister. Some 22 people stand charged in the cases, including former BNP state minister Abdus Salam Pintu, his brother Maolana Tajuddin, also the alleged grenade supplier, and Mufti Hannan, leader of banned Islamist outfit Harkat-ul-Jihad-al-Islami. Of them, 13 accused including Pintu and Hannan are now behind bars while the remaining accused are on the run. The Criminal Investigation Department pressed charges in two cases, a murder case and an explosives case, on June 11 last year. Some 61 among 412 witnesses have so far testified. The witnesses include president Zillur Rahman, prime minister Sheikh Hasina, home minister Sahara Khatun and AL's former general secretary Abdul Jalil. bdnews24.
